If you want three separate state files

Since you said:

Dev
Test
Prod

must all have different state files, do not rely on workspaces for state separation.

Instead use three backend configuration files.

backend-dev.hcl
resource_group_name  = "terraform-rg"
storage_account_name = "tfstorage001"
container_name       = "tfstate"

key = "dev.tfstate"
backend-test.hcl
resource_group_name  = "terraform-rg"
storage_account_name = "tfstorage001"
container_name       = "tfstate"

key = "test.tfstate"
backend-prod.hcl
resource_group_name  = "terraform-rg"
storage_account_name = "tfstorage001"
container_name       = "tfstate"

key = "prod.tfstate"

Then initialize with the appropriate backend:

terraform init -reconfigure \
-backend-config=backend-dev.hcl

or

terraform init -reconfigure \
-backend-config=backend-test.hcl

or

terraform init -reconfigure \
-backend-config=backend-prod.hcl

In this model, you don't need workspaces at all.
